# IDE-Like UX Overhaul — Non-Intimidating for Non-Technical Users

Transform VibeMarketer from a simple sidebar+form app into an **IDE-like workspace** (inspired by Zed/VSCode layout) — but designed so a marketer or PM would never feel intimidated. No code, no terminal, no technical jargon.

## Core Design Principles

1. **IDE structure, human language** — Activity bar, tabs, panels, status bar — but everything says "skills", "outputs", "workspace" instead of "files", "terminal", "console"
2. **Zero code visibility** — Skills are friendly cards, outputs are polished documents
3. **Progressive disclosure** — Simple by default, powerful on demand

## Layout Architecture

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Activity Bar │  Tabs (open skills)                       │
│ (left icons) │──────────────────────────────────────────│
│              │                                           │
│  🏠 Home     │  Main Editor Panel                        │
│  🧰 Skills   │  (Skill form OR output document)          │
│  📊 History  │                                           │
│  ⚙️ Settings │                                           │
│              │                                           │
│              ├───────────────────────────────────────────│
│              │  Status Bar (bottom)                      │
└──────────────┴───────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

